The paper deals with the design of regenerating codes for distributed storage systems, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The use of resolvable designs and combinatorial structures also suggests a connection to discrete mathematics and combinatorics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the implementation of the codes, which could fall under systems and network architecture (cs.SI) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
